                    <br>
                  <h4 style="color: #6ABD45" class="text-center"><i style="text-align: center;" class="fa fa-star fa"></i> <i style="text-align: center;" class="fa fa-star fa"></i> <i style="text-align: center;" class="fa fa-star fa"></i> <i style="text-align: center;" class="fa fa-star fa"></i> </h4>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact Section -->
    <section id="contact">
        <div class="container">

            <h2 class="text-center">The Characters</h2>
             <br><br>
             
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-right"></i> Swipe or keypress in the <i style="color: #EC5825">right</i> direction if the post you just read has you feeling amused, happy or just puts a smile on your face.</p>
        
                    <%= image_tag("2.png", class: "img-responsive") %>

                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-down"></i> Not every post will have you laughing. If you react feeling sympathetic just push it <i style="color: #19C0D9">down</i> and a new post will load straight away.</p>
                    
                    <%= image_tag("3.png", class: "img-responsive") %>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-left"></i> Sometimes you will get angry or annoyed, that's just part of weacting. Just swipe in the <i style="color: #D14646">left</i> direction and take a deep breath. </p>
                    <%= image_tag("4.png", class: "img-responsive") %>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-up"></i> Meh. Blah. Huh? Those are completely normal reactions to have. Swipe <i style="color: #009344">up</i> when a post has you confused, ambivilent, or even a little disgusted. </p>
                    <%= image_tag("1.png", class: "img-responsive") %>
                </div>
                
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- About Section -->
